HEADWORD: Censorial
<hw>Cen*so"ri*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Belonging to a censor, or to the correction of public morals.</def>
<rj><au>Junius.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Full of censure; censorious.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>censorial</qex> declamation of Juvenal.</q> <rj><qau>T.
Warton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Censorian</ent>⟦br⟧
